    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using `:hide Man foo` in a buffer with `bufhidden=wipe` set, the plugin attempts to restore the `tagfunc` option of the wiped buffer, causing an invalid buffer id error to be emitted.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`foo` doesn't need to exist, but it doesn't occur with an unnamed buffer.\r\n```\r\nnvim --clean foo\r\n:set bufhidden=wipe\r\n:hide Man ls\r\n/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/man.lua:742: Invalid buffer id: 1\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nShould not error (check if `buf` is valid after jumping before attempting to restore options)\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-674+g0346666f7\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\n`neovim-nightly-bin` AUR package (downloads latest github release)",
